  "prompt": "How do I report fake app on Appstore?",
  "response": "To report a fake or inappropriate app on the App Store, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the App Store on your iOS device\n\n2. Find the app you want to report\n\n3. Scroll down to the bottom of the app page\n\n4. Tap \"Report a Concern\" or tap on the app's rating and scroll to the bottom\n\n5. Choose the reason for reporting, such as:\n- Inappropriate content\n- Spam\n- Copycat app\n- Potential scam\n\n6. Select specific details about your concern\n\n7. Submit the report\n\nAlternatively, you can report an app through Apple's website:\n1. Go to https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/reportapps/\n2. Fill out the reporting form with details about the app\n3. Submit the report\n\nIf you believe an app is a scam or potentially harmful, you can also contact Apple Support directly for further assistance.\n\nTips:\n- Provide as much detail as possible\n- Include screenshots if helpful\n- Be specific about why you believe the app is fake or inappropriate",
